---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms and Conditions - BlissBox">
  <Navbar />
  
  <main class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="glass-card policy-card">
        <h1 class="gradient-text">Terms and Conditions</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: May 9, 2026</p>
        
        <div class="policy-content">
          <section>
            <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
            <p>By downloading or using BlissBox, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the application.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
            <p>BlissBox is a third-party client for music streaming services (including YouTube Music). It provides a custom interface for accessing public content, switching between audio/video modes, and managing local playback.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>BlissBox is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or in any way officially connected to Google or YouTube Music. Your use of BlissBox is also subject to the terms of service of the respective streaming providers you access through the app. You are responsible for complying with their terms.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>4. User Responsibilities</h2>
            <p>You agree not to use BlissBox for any illegal purposes or to violate the intellectual property rights of others. BlissBox is provided for personal, non-commercial use only.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>5. No Warranties</h2>
            <p>BlissBox is provided "as is" and "as available" without any warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee that the service will be uninterrupted or error-free. Streaming availability depends on third-party APIs which we do not control.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, BlissBox and its developers shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages resulting from your use of the application.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>7. Changes to Terms</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Your continued use of the app after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the new terms.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    padding-top: 10rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .policy-card {
    padding: 4rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .policy-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-card {
      padding: 2rem;
    }
    
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
